1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
What is SOR?

2
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:09,820
SOR is short for science of reading. It is neurologically proven research on the five stages of English acquisition.

3
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:14,160
It's currently endorsed by the governments of the US, Canada,

4
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:17,080
England, and Australia.

5
00:00:17,639 --> 00:00:21,160
It's not linked to whether you're a native English speaker or not.

6
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:27,200
But as long as you're learning English, your brain will inevitably go through these five stages.

7
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:37,520
In Taiwan, the syllabus to learn English starts unreasonably on the second stage of English acquisition.

8
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:43,919
And often parents request children to skip even further ahead and memorize vocabularies,

9
00:00:44,279 --> 00:00:47,500
which is actually the fourth stage of English acquisition.

10
00:00:48,139 --> 00:00:55,200
What's worse is how parents flock to the idea of an all-English environment at school and send their children

11
00:00:55,720 --> 00:00:59,320
unprepared directly to the fifth stage of English learning.

12
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:01,680
comprehension.

13
00:01:01,680 --> 00:01:06,320
And when children are not learning the right way and skipping the basics,

14
00:01:06,559 --> 00:01:11,040
it's difficult and almost impossible to acquire English skills at all.

15
00:01:11,599 --> 00:01:15,120
The first stage of English acquisition is called PA,

16
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:18,120
which stands for phonemic awareness.

17
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:22,160
Do you know how many sounds can be found in the English language?

18
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:27,339
There are 26 letters of the alphabet, so there must be 26 sounds, right?

19
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:34,459
The correct answer is actually 44 sounds, which is also known as 44 phonemes.

20
00:01:34,459 --> 00:01:36,459
If you only know this now,

21
00:01:36,660 --> 00:01:42,900
it's normal. The Taiwanese English education skips this important step of English learning entirely.

22
00:01:43,260 --> 00:01:45,419
There are three levels to training for PA.

23
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:50,779
The first level is to hear and perceive the 44 English phonemes.

24
00:01:51,139 --> 00:01:55,739
Our brains need to take stock of the 44 sounds that are found in English and

25
00:01:56,059 --> 00:01:58,300
not just the 26 letters of the alphabet.

26
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:04,180
The second level of learning PA is to sound out the 44 phonemes.

27
00:02:04,540 --> 00:02:08,699
It is essential to be able to pronounce all 44 phonemes

28
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:13,779
accurately. And by now, our PA training is halfway there.

29
00:02:14,699 --> 00:02:18,820
The third level is to link up the 44 phonemes into

30
00:02:19,419 --> 00:02:21,419
consonant, vowel,

31
00:02:21,539 --> 00:02:26,979
consonant sound combinations, which is also known as CVC combinations.

32
00:02:27,419 --> 00:02:29,419
This will result in a total of

33
00:02:30,419 --> 00:02:33,660
60,200 different sound combinations.

34
00:02:34,220 --> 00:02:39,979
Only when you've learned but not memorized and can hear and perceive and pronounce all

35
00:02:40,619 --> 00:02:46,940
60,200 CVC combinations, can you move on to the next stage of English acquisition.

36
00:02:47,779 --> 00:02:49,779
Phonics.

37
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:56,740
In America, children are fully immersed in an all-English environment for six years before they start school.

38
00:02:57,380 --> 00:03:04,539
When they start school, they start with the basics of PA, even though it's their seventh year being exposed to English.

39
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:08,979
As opposed to children in Taiwan, who speak Mandarin before they start school,

40
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:13,220
have their first exposure to English when they start elementary school.

41
00:03:13,699 --> 00:03:16,380
And that's all the more reason for them to learn English,

42
00:03:17,020 --> 00:03:19,020
starting with PA.

43
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:25,860
Phonics. This is the stage where the 26 letters of the English alphabet come in. The study of phonics

44
00:03:26,179 --> 00:03:29,699
establishes the correspondence between the English alphabet and the

45
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:32,660
60,200 sounds of spoken English

46
00:03:32,940 --> 00:03:35,460
learned during the PA stage.

47
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:39,940
An example of establishing letter-to-sound correspondence is this.

48
00:03:49,419 --> 00:03:51,059
Bed.

49
00:03:51,059 --> 00:03:54,539
First graders in Taiwan start English the wrong way.

50
00:03:54,539 --> 00:03:59,380
And that's why learning English becomes a painful and difficult journey for them.

51
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:06,259
Their teachers may only know the 26 letters of the alphabet and are unaware of the 44 phonemes.

52
00:04:06,860 --> 00:04:09,020
So they will most likely teach like this.

53
00:04:19,540 --> 00:04:21,540
And

54
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:23,339
all the while,

55
00:04:23,339 --> 00:04:27,299
children are also required to memorize the definition for bed.

56
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:32,500
Keep in mind, the vocabulary is on the fourth stage of English acquisition.

57
00:04:33,059 --> 00:04:39,019
By asking children with absolutely no English skills to jump to the fourth stage of English acquisition

58
00:04:39,420 --> 00:04:41,459
will only be a cause for pain.

59
00:04:42,980 --> 00:04:44,260
Fluency.

60
00:04:44,299 --> 00:04:48,579
Fluency means the ability to read effortlessly. At this stage,

61
00:04:48,579 --> 00:04:52,420
you should be able to read an English article quickly and accurately.

62
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:57,859
You may not need to know the meaning or grammar of the article, but you should be able to read it.

63
00:04:58,619 --> 00:05:06,179
The reason why you don't need to know the meaning and grammar is because at this stage, the focus is solely on training fluency.

64
00:05:07,059 --> 00:05:11,980
Spending time learning meaning and grammar would be a distraction to practicing fluency.

65
00:05:12,820 --> 00:05:16,899
Have you ever tried reading an English article and noticed yourself pausing,

66
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:20,420
confused, and not quite sure how to read a certain word?

67
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:22,619
Why is that?

68
00:05:22,619 --> 00:05:27,899
It's because very few Taiwanese children have the training to read English quickly and accurately.

69
00:05:29,059 --> 00:05:32,779
Fluency is essential for the next stage, which is vocabulary.

70
00:05:33,260 --> 00:05:38,579
If you don't have the basic skills for fluency, it is impossible to remember vocabulary.

71
00:05:39,299 --> 00:05:43,500
Once you've established the basics of PA, phonics, and fluency,

72
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:49,220
congratulations! You've earned the ticket to start learning vocabulary. At this stage,

73
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:52,739
you can start to learn the meaning of words and grammar.

74
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:56,660
And now, you'll see how quickly you internalize your learnings.

75
00:05:56,660 --> 00:06:01,579
And it's because you're well trained in the first three stages of SOR.

76
00:06:02,179 --> 00:06:08,019
When Taiwanese parents ask their children without the skills in the first three stages of SOR

77
00:06:08,339 --> 00:06:11,339
to start learning English by memorizing words,

78
00:06:11,339 --> 00:06:19,859
it makes learning more difficult and this will only cost children to lose confidence and dislike English even more.

79
00:06:20,899 --> 00:06:24,459
When you've reached comprehension, that's when the real fun begins.

80
00:06:25,019 --> 00:06:28,859
Because comprehension includes popular culture and the classics.

81
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:33,140
From English poems to lyrics, to Grammy award winners,

82
00:06:33,540 --> 00:06:37,459
from Disney cartoons to the different brands of popular cereals,

83
00:06:37,820 --> 00:06:43,700
from a humorous joke to articles talking about environmental issues, and more.

84
00:06:44,140 --> 00:06:49,779
At this stage, you'll find English is fun and the possibilities are endless.

85
00:06:50,299 --> 00:06:53,820
By then, you'll be able to make friends using English.

86
00:06:54,700 --> 00:07:01,540
But before all that, the first four stages are indispensable skills that are required for you to get there.

87
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:03,899
To conclude,

88
00:07:03,899 --> 00:07:07,779
SOR is endorsed by the governments of the US, Canada,

89
00:07:08,339 --> 00:07:14,980
England, and Australia. And it's even proven by neuroscience to be the best way to learn English.

90
00:07:15,940 --> 00:07:19,739
Taiwanese children deserve to acquire English this way too.

91
00:07:19,739 --> 00:07:27,220
To learn more about the total solution on the five stages of SOR, please visit us here.

92
00:07:49,739 --> 00:07:52,739
You


